<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E59C516FF3FBC2EFB0AEEF6" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E59C516FF3FBC2EFB0AEEF6" blockId="91.[151,1436,793,1033]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FF3FBC2EFE97EE3D" bold="true" box="[199,321,829,854]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
Moderate sized (
<quantity id="AB3EEEE55E59C516FDF9BC2EFD5FEE3E" box="[513,649,829,853]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.2" metricValueMax="8.9" metricValueMin="7.5" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" unit="mm" value="8.2" valueMax="8.9" valueMin="7.5">7.5–8.9 mm</quantity>
long); pronotum, MS and MN orange; elytra dark brown; LO entire in V7; dimple and hump absent; very similar to 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FD61BC72FBD9EE12" authority="(Olivier)" baseAuthorityName="Olivier" box="[665,1039,865,889]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennata">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FD61BC72FC75EE12" box="[665,931,865,889]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Medeopteryx antennata</emphasis>
(Olivier)
</taxonomicName>
, distinguished by the outline of the terminal abdomen and elytral apex and the uniformly dark antennae (
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E59C516FC65BC96FBB5EEF6" author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[925,1123,901,925]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="117 - 170" refId="ref122195" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 a) Further Revisional Studies on the firefly genus Pteroptyx Olivier (Coleoptera: Lampyridae: Luciolinae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 117 - 170." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne 1987a</bibRefCitation>
<figureCitation id="F4FD5F855E59C516FB93BC96FB19EEF6" box="[1131,1231,901,925]" captionStart="FIGURES 3–5" captionStartId="10.[151,263,1921,1944]" captionTargetBox="[290,1309,181,1907]" captionTargetId="figure-108@10.[282,1309,173,1922]" captionTargetPageId="10" captionText="FIGURES 3–5. Majority rule tree for the complete analysis of the Luciolinae. Analysis consisted of consensus of 169 MPTs with a length of 5609 from a data set of 143 taxa and 436 morphological characters in (see Table 3). Figure 3, part 1: nodes 1– 34; 4, part 2 Nodes 35–52; 5, part 3 nodes 55–76. Nodes (red). New genera, new species, and still undescribed species in red and bold, with identification numbers blue. Black values above branches show the % of MPTs over 50 %." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5265348" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5265348/files/figure.png" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Figs 3, 4</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="24DC108B5E59C516FF3FBCBAFD39E962" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6C7943005E59C516FF3FBCBAFD39E962" blockId="91.[151,1436,793,1033]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FF3FBCBAFEEDEEAA" bold="true" box="[199,315,937,961]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Remarks.</emphasis>
The specimens included by 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E59C516FD78BCBAFC5AEEAA" author="Ballantyne, L. A." box="[640,908,937,961]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="171 - 188" refId="ref122235" refString="Ballantyne, L. A. (1987 b) Lucioline Morphology, Taxonomy and Behaviour: A Reappraisal. (Coleoptera, Lampyridae). Transactions of the American Entomological Society, 113, 171 - 188." type="journal article" year="1987">Ballantyne (1987b:159)</bibRefCitation>
in the 
<typeStatus id="B37DFDA25E59C516FC24BCB9FBDAEEA9" box="[988,1036,938,962]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">type</typeStatus>
series of this species were initially included by 
<bibRefCitation id="08573EF15E59C516FED1BCDEFE18EE8E" author="Lloyd, J. E." box="[297,462,973,997]" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" pagination="991 - 1008" refId="ref127038" refString="Lloyd, J. E. (1973 a) Fireflies of Melanesia: Bioluminescence, Mating Behavior, and Synchronous flashing. Environmental Entomology, 2 (no. 6), 991 - 1008." type="journal article" year="1973">Lloyd (1973a)</bibRefCitation>
in 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FE02BCDDFDB0EE8E" box="[506,614,974,997]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Pteroptyx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FE02BCDDFDB0EE8E" box="[506,614,974,997]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Pteroptyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(now 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FD4DBCDEFC91EE8E" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" box="[693,839,973,997]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FD4DBCDEFC91EE8E" box="[693,839,973,997]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">Medeopteryx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
) 
<taxonomicName id="ABC638835E59C516FCA3BCDDFC1DEE8E" authorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" authorityYear="2013" baseAuthorityName="Ballantyne &amp; Lambkin" baseAuthorityYear="2013" box="[859,971,974,997]" class="Insecta" family="Lampyridae" genus="Medeopteryx" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="91" pageNumber="92" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="antennata">
<emphasis id="5EB29F125E59C516FCA3BCDDFC1DEE8E" box="[859,971,974,997]" italics="true" pageId="91" pageNumber="92">antennata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
on the basis of their flashing data, and similarities with that species are discussed elsewhere.
</paragraph>
